    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="492" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Scruggs</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 19,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 85.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose, for your information and the files
                        of your legation, copy of Mr. Lincoln’s No. 229<note n="*" xml:id="d492fn1">See correspondence with the legation of the United States at
                            London.</note> of the 5th instant, reporting his conversation with Lord
                        Salisbury in regard to the renewal of diplomatic relations between Great
                        Britain and Venezuela and the settlement of the boundary dispute by
                        arbitration.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
